<p>tale it went off accidently &amp; shot him in the foot, I don't know how he will get on, a D.C.M. I expect for self inflicted wounding.<br/>Had the same stunt over again this afternoon &amp; General Walker was there for the "March past".  Last night Fred Shannon came back  he was gazetted to this Batt.<br/>21st. Church parade this morning but it was very short<br/>This afternoon our Battalion is playing the 3rd "Soccer" &amp; "Rugby" This evening the church bells were ringing down at the little church at Beauveaux, &amp; they sounded beautifully  so clear &amp; ringing were the tones that came softly over the snow white fields, but I suppose that the rarity of the cold air had a lot to do with the mellow-</p>
